Minister of Justice Ronald Lamola is taking a no-nonsense approach to guns in court. Court roll management challenges at the Johannesburg Magistrate's Court were relayed to new Justice Minister Ronald Lamola on Thursday, after rival gangs faced off in the court's corridors on Wednesday. The gang members, from Westbury in Johannesburg, were there to support their respective leaders whose cases were placed on the court roll in different courtrooms on the same day. Watch more: Chaos as rival Westbury gangs face off in Joburg court.